  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2005-02-03",
    "date": "2005-03-09T16:11:55Z",
    "text": "Social Security Right To Know Act - Amends the Social Security Act to require Social Security account statements to contain additional information, such as: (1) a statement of the current Social Security tax rates applicable to wages and self-employment income, including an indication of the combined total of such rates of employee and employer taxes with respect to wages; and (2) a comparison of total annual Social Security tax inflows with the total annual benefits paid."
